video-distill
=============

This project builds a Kinetics -> prompt-corpus captioning pipeline used to
adapt video diffusion models (WAN2.2) for streaming inference (StreamDiffusion
v2). It stands on the work of others; attribution below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Kinetics dataset
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Kinetics Human Action Video Dataset was created by DeepMind.
  Kay et al., "The Kinetics Human Action Video Dataset", arXiv:1705.06950.
  Carreira et al., Kinetics-600 / Kinetics-700 follow-ups.
  https://deepmind.com/research/open-source/kinetics

Dataset hosting and the original downloader/extractor shell scripts
(`k*_downloader.sh`, `k*_extractor.sh`, `arrange_by_classes.py`) are provided by
the Common Visual Data Foundation (CVDF):
  https://github.com/cvdfoundation/kinetics-dataset
Those upstream scripts and all contributors to that repository retain their
original authorship. Files derived from or depending on that repo are used in
accordance with its terms.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Models referenced
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Qwen3-VL (Alibaba / Qwen team) is used as the video captioner. WAN2.1 / WAN2.2
are referenced as the video-generation models being adapted. These are the
property of their respective authors and are used under their own licenses.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This repository's own additions
